Peru ' s January coffee output falls to 15 tonnes . Peru ' s January coffee production fell to 15 tonnes from 62 tonnes in the same month last year , the Agriculture Ministry said Tuesday . Non - decaffeinated coffee exports fell 68 . 6 percent in December to $ 5 . 1 million , while total exports last year fell 21 . 5 percent from 1995 to $ 222 . 6 million , the ministry added in its monthly report . The ministry did not give export figures for January . Peru , whose principal coffee harvest is between April and November , is South America ' s number four producer after Brazil , Colombia and Ecuador , according to the government . ( ( - - Saul Hudson , Lima newsroom , 511 221 - 2134 ) ) 
